1
00:00:01,436 --> 00:00:03,028
I get Ava Hessington acquitted,

2
00:00:03,437 --> 00:00:05,105
Darby backs me
for managing partner.

3
00:00:05,189 --> 00:00:07,774
I don't want it anymore.
Get out of my sight.

4
00:00:07,858 --> 00:00:09,559
You called Mariga
to offer him a bribe.

5
00:00:09,610 --> 00:00:10,744
Doesn't matter--
Danny should never have

6
00:00:10,828 --> 00:00:11,828
had him in the first place.

7
00:00:11,895 --> 00:00:12,862
But he does now.

8
00:00:12,914 --> 00:00:15,081
You're saying
he traced my call.

9
00:00:15,166 --> 00:00:18,084
You're suing me for ownership
of the Mikado?

10
00:00:18,169 --> 00:00:20,236
He said he might as well
have left his cat

11
00:00:20,288 --> 00:00:22,339
with Michael Vick.

12
00:00:22,406 --> 00:00:23,873
I'm offering you
a settlement.

13
00:00:23,925 --> 00:00:27,177
He get back the associates,
I get back my cat.

14
00:00:27,244 --> 00:00:28,878
Clifford Danner is 18.

15
00:00:28,930 --> 00:00:31,681
I put him in jail 12 years ago.
He's innocent.

16
00:00:31,749 --> 00:00:32,915
Cameron buried the evidence.

17
00:00:32,967 --> 00:00:34,768
Emmanuel Mariga,
20 years ago

18
00:00:34,852 --> 00:00:37,220
at the University of Cape Town
on the rugby team.

19
00:00:37,271 --> 00:00:39,189
You know who else played rugby?
Stephen Huntley.

20
00:00:39,256 --> 00:00:41,024
Stephen was the one
who ordered those killings.

21
00:00:41,091 --> 00:00:42,776
I'm so sorry, Harvey.

22
00:00:46,280 --> 00:00:47,697
Aah!

23
00:00:54,438 --> 00:00:56,406
[Winces]

24
00:00:56,457 --> 00:00:58,875
Tell me he looks worse.

25
00:00:58,942 --> 00:01:01,995
He does.

26
00:01:02,079 --> 00:01:04,297
Are you hurt?

27
00:01:04,382 --> 00:01:06,166
No, I'm fine.

28
00:01:08,619 --> 00:01:10,387
I hope you didn't do that
because of me.

29
00:01:10,454 --> 00:01:13,556
It was a fight, Donna,
not a duel.

30
00:01:15,259 --> 00:01:18,928
- How could I not have--
- Listen to me.

31
00:01:18,980 --> 00:01:21,798
Stephen betrayed us all.

32
00:01:21,849 --> 00:01:23,433
You don't understand,
Harvey.

33
00:01:23,484 --> 00:01:26,636
I was with him.

34
00:01:26,687 --> 00:01:28,772
And he was capable
of something like that,

35
00:01:28,823 --> 00:01:30,190
and I didn't even see it.

36
00:01:30,274 --> 00:01:32,609
You know, I'm supposed to--
Donna!

37
00:01:32,660 --> 00:01:34,577
[Sighs]

38
00:01:34,645 --> 00:01:36,312
It's okay.

39
00:01:36,364 --> 00:01:38,865
Just tell me
you're gonna make him pay.

40
00:01:38,949 --> 00:01:42,202
He'll pay.

41
00:01:50,628 --> 00:01:53,463
Let's not talk about it.

42
00:01:53,514 --> 00:01:56,516
Talk about what?

43
00:01:56,600 --> 00:01:58,301
What do you need me to do?

44
00:01:58,352 --> 00:01:59,969
I need you to keep going
with everything you have

45
00:02:00,021 --> 00:02:01,504
to impeach
Mariga's testimony.

46
00:02:01,555 --> 00:02:02,689
What about the stuff
on Stephen?

47
00:02:02,773 --> 00:02:04,507
- Not yet.
- Why not?

48
00:02:04,558 --> 00:02:05,892
Because we don't have proof.

49
00:02:05,976 --> 00:02:07,027
The trial's in two days.

50
00:02:07,111 --> 00:02:08,228
We should bring Ava in
and tell her--

51
00:02:08,312 --> 00:02:09,229
- Not yet.
- Why not?

52
00:02:09,313 --> 00:02:10,280
Because we don't have proof.

53
00:02:10,347 --> 00:02:11,587
Harvey, we have
to do something.

54
00:02:11,649 --> 00:02:13,010
And how would
that conversation go?

55
00:02:13,016 --> 00:02:15,118
"Hi, Ava, turns out
one of the lawyers from our firm

56
00:02:15,185 --> 00:02:16,953
"is trying to frame you
for a crime he committed.

57
00:02:17,020 --> 00:02:19,355
But right now we're not sure
we can do anything about it."

58
00:02:19,407 --> 00:02:20,957
What are you gonna do?

59
00:02:21,024 --> 00:02:22,525
I'm gonna go home,
get a good night's sleep,

60
00:02:22,576 --> 00:02:23,743
and then tomorrow
I'm gonna find out

61
00:02:23,828 --> 00:02:24,911
what the whole story is.

62
00:02:24,995 --> 00:02:26,395
Harvey, Stephen
isn't gonna tell you

63
00:02:26,414 --> 00:02:27,714
what the whole story is.

64
00:02:27,798 --> 00:02:30,199
No, but there's
someone else who can.

65
00:02:32,336 --> 00:02:34,203
You knew this case
was heading your way

66
00:02:34,255 --> 00:02:35,588
before you ever
came after us.

67
00:02:35,673 --> 00:02:37,173
That's why
you wanted to merge.

68
00:02:37,224 --> 00:02:38,425
Yes, it is.

69
00:02:38,509 --> 00:02:40,269
And I regret the situation
as much as you do.

70
00:02:40,311 --> 00:02:41,728
But what's done is done.

71
00:02:41,812 --> 00:02:43,813
Is that what you told Stephen
when you found out he did it?

72
00:02:43,881 --> 00:02:44,981
Found out?

73
00:02:45,048 --> 00:02:46,599
How do we know
he didn't order it?

74
00:02:46,684 --> 00:02:48,384
Because I am giving you
my word.

75
00:02:48,436 --> 00:02:50,570
Why should we trust a man
who sent Stephen over here

76
00:02:50,654 --> 00:02:52,072
to cover his ass?

77
00:02:52,156 --> 00:02:55,525
I sent Stephen over here
because I care about Ava,

78
00:02:55,576 --> 00:02:58,227
which is why I sent him to
the E.I.R. in the first place.

79
00:02:58,279 --> 00:03:00,580
I had no idea
he would do what he did,

80
00:03:00,664 --> 00:03:02,799
and I have been trying
to fix it ever since.

81
00:03:02,867 --> 00:03:05,168
- Then fix it right now.
- And how exactly can I do that?

82
00:03:05,236 --> 00:03:06,803
By stating in court

83
00:03:06,871 --> 00:03:09,205
Stephen acted alone
without Ava's knowledge.

84
00:03:09,273 --> 00:03:10,840
- I can't.
- Why not?

85
00:03:10,908 --> 00:03:12,292
Because he never told me.

86
00:03:12,376 --> 00:03:15,345
And you never asked because
you never wanted to know.

87
00:03:15,412 --> 00:03:17,180
You piece of shit.

88
00:03:17,247 --> 00:03:19,099
You care about Ava
so much.

89
00:03:19,183 --> 00:03:21,083
How could you
do this to her?

90
00:03:21,135 --> 00:03:23,303
I wasn't doing anything
to her.

91
00:03:23,387 --> 00:03:25,755
I was trying to do
something for her.

92
00:03:25,806 --> 00:03:29,125
Remind me never to ask you
for any favors.

93
00:03:29,193 --> 00:03:31,027
Well, I'm not asking
for a favor.

94
00:03:31,094 --> 00:03:33,446
But you are going to agree
to do something right now.

95
00:03:33,531 --> 00:03:36,316
And what is that?

96
00:03:36,400 --> 00:03:38,201
[Keys clacking]

97
00:03:38,268 --> 00:03:40,203
[Computer beeps]

98
00:03:44,575 --> 00:03:47,127
It's not gonna work.

99
00:03:47,211 --> 00:03:50,130
I cut you off
to get your attention.

100
00:03:50,214 --> 00:03:52,215
[Sighs]

101
00:03:52,282 --> 00:03:54,050
Well, you have it.

102
00:03:54,117 --> 00:03:57,003
Good, 'cause I just have
one question for you.

103
00:03:57,087 --> 00:03:58,922
How can you live
with yourself?

104
00:03:58,973 --> 00:04:00,757
- What?
- You know what?

105
00:04:00,808 --> 00:04:02,175
I don't have any questions
for you.

106
00:04:02,259 --> 00:04:04,293
I just came in here to let
you know that you make me sick.

107
00:04:04,345 --> 00:04:06,896
Obviously
I hurt you, Donna,

108
00:04:06,964 --> 00:04:08,982
and I never meant
to do that.

109
00:04:09,066 --> 00:04:10,400
Oh, you didn't hurt me.

110
00:04:10,467 --> 00:04:12,569
You just made me somebody
who slept with a murderer.

111
00:04:12,636 --> 00:04:15,355
Murderer?

112
00:04:15,439 --> 00:04:17,357
I don't know
what you think you know,

113
00:04:17,441 --> 00:04:20,493
but those people that
were killed were terrorists.

114
00:04:20,578 --> 00:04:21,744
They were people...

115
00:04:21,812 --> 00:04:23,479
Who lived on top
of something that you wanted.

116
00:04:23,531 --> 00:04:26,332
People who had guns--
murderers, Donna.

117
00:04:26,417 --> 00:04:28,751
Now, if you're so appalled
by how business is done,

118
00:04:28,819 --> 00:04:30,253
may I suggest
that you return

119
00:04:30,320 --> 00:04:33,339
all of your designer clothes
that you look so ravishing in,

120
00:04:33,424 --> 00:04:35,175
because they're paid for

121
00:04:35,259 --> 00:04:37,293
by the dirty work
this firm does.

122
00:04:37,344 --> 00:04:38,678
We don't kill people.

123
00:04:38,762 --> 00:04:41,130
You mean chemical companies
that Harvey represents

124
00:04:41,182 --> 00:04:43,216
or car companies
that Harvey defends?

125
00:04:43,300 --> 00:04:47,020
How about insurance providers
whose claims he helps deny?

126
00:04:47,104 --> 00:04:50,172
- Don't bring him into this.
- He's always been in this.

127
00:04:50,224 --> 00:04:52,058
You know what?
I've had enough of this.

128
00:04:52,142 --> 00:04:54,777
I didn't really cut off your
shit to get your attention.

129
00:04:54,845 --> 00:04:58,948
I cut it off because
you don't need it anymore.

130
00:04:59,016 --> 00:05:00,366
You're fired.

131
00:05:01,685 --> 00:05:03,620
Harvey
would never allow that.

132
00:05:03,687 --> 00:05:06,239
Edward Darby signed
your pink slip an hour ago.

133
00:05:12,997 --> 00:05:16,633
♪ See the money,
wanna stay for your meal ♪

134
00:05:16,700 --> 00:05:19,969
♪ get another piece of pie
for your wife ♪

135
00:05:20,037 --> 00:05:23,139
♪ everybody wanna know
how it feel ♪

136
00:05:23,206 --> 00:05:26,893
♪ everybody wanna see
what it's like ♪

137
00:05:26,977 --> 00:05:29,812
♪ living in a beehive
of your mind ♪

138
00:05:29,880 --> 00:05:32,379
♪ me and missus
so busy, busy making money ♪

139
