143
00:05:45,312 --> 00:05:47,914
2 months, 5 days, and 3 hours
under Nigel's tutelage,

144
00:05:47,940 --> 00:05:49,541
and this is what
you have to show for it?

145
00:05:49,736 --> 00:05:51,654
That's over 20 motions.

146
00:05:51,738 --> 00:05:52,988
20 dog shits.

147
00:05:53,073 --> 00:05:54,790
Did you get this
out of a Grisham novel?

148
00:05:54,875 --> 00:05:56,108
Because that's fiction.

149
00:05:56,159 --> 00:05:57,827
And you...

150
00:05:57,911 --> 00:06:00,129
My mother can get
this motion thrown out.

151
00:06:00,213 --> 00:06:02,114
And you--well, you're gone
anyway in two days.

152
00:06:02,165 --> 00:06:03,249
Listen up, people.

153
00:06:03,300 --> 00:06:06,502
I've reviewed your work
in my absence.

154
00:06:06,586 --> 00:06:08,304
And guess what.

155
00:06:08,388 --> 00:06:09,788
It's pathetic.

156
00:06:09,840 --> 00:06:13,008
Every stinking one of you
should get down on your knees

157
00:06:13,093 --> 00:06:14,510
and thank God and me

158
00:06:14,594 --> 00:06:16,962
for letting you continue
to exist in our kingdoms.

159
00:06:20,133 --> 00:06:22,151
Louis, what was that about?
What's going on?

160
00:06:22,235 --> 00:06:23,635
It was about me letting
these assholes know

161
00:06:23,687 --> 00:06:25,637
who's in charge.
They know you're in charge.

162
00:06:25,689 --> 00:06:28,407
They put you in charge.
They didn't put me in shit.

163
00:06:28,474 --> 00:06:30,526
They sat there in judgment while
my character got ripped apart,

164
00:06:30,610 --> 00:06:32,811
and not one of them
lifted a single finger to help.

165
00:06:32,863 --> 00:06:35,364
They ruled in your favor.
They chose you over Nigel.

166
00:06:35,448 --> 00:06:39,818
No, they made me
give up Mikado for them.

167
00:06:39,870 --> 00:06:44,089
Okay, you're displacing your
anger over Mikado onto them.

168
00:06:44,157 --> 00:06:47,376
They didn't put you
in this position.

169
00:06:47,460 --> 00:06:48,878
It's not fair.

170
00:06:48,962 --> 00:06:50,045
You're right.

171
00:06:50,130 --> 00:06:52,831
They didn't put me
in this position,

172
00:06:52,883 --> 00:06:53,966
but I know who did.

173
00:06:54,017 --> 00:06:55,384
Goddamn Darby--

174
00:06:55,468 --> 00:06:57,428
unleashes his dog, leaves us
to clean up the mess.

175
00:06:57,437 --> 00:06:58,804
We can still go after Mariga
in court.

176
00:06:58,855 --> 00:07:00,172
I mean,
he's an admitted murderer

177
00:07:00,223 --> 00:07:01,690
who cut a deal
to save his life.

178
00:07:01,775 --> 00:07:03,025
Wait a second.

179
00:07:03,109 --> 00:07:04,777
That deal is only good
if he's telling the truth.

180
00:07:04,844 --> 00:07:06,812
We can't go after him
with the truth on the stand.

181
00:07:06,863 --> 00:07:10,015
Maybe, but we can go after him
with the truth not on the stand.

182
00:07:10,066 --> 00:07:12,017
Cameron would have
to be willing to listen.

183
00:07:12,068 --> 00:07:13,402
Then I better
get him to listen.

184
00:07:13,486 --> 00:07:14,787
And I better
go after Mariga.

185
00:07:14,854 --> 00:07:16,855
- And change your clothes.
- What? Why?

186
00:07:16,907 --> 00:07:18,991
If they see a lawyer
within 20 yards of that lobby,

187
00:07:19,042 --> 00:07:21,526
they'll lock the place down.

188
00:07:21,578 --> 00:07:24,529
[Rock music]

189
00:07:24,581 --> 00:07:32,537
♪

190
00:07:53,777 --> 00:07:56,829
- Oh, you're not room service.
- No, I'm not, but...

191
00:07:56,896 --> 00:07:58,864
I do need to talk
to Colonel Mariga.

192
00:07:58,915 --> 00:08:01,533
And I need to stop paying
alimony to my cheating ex-wife,

193
00:08:01,584 --> 00:08:03,402
but that's not going
to happen.

194
00:08:03,453 --> 00:08:04,954
If you let me in,
maybe I can make that happen.

195
00:08:05,038 --> 00:08:07,673
And how the hell are you
gonna make that happen?

196
00:08:07,740 --> 00:08:10,509
I'm a lawyer.

197
00:08:10,576 --> 00:08:12,044
You don't look like
a lawyer to me.

198
00:08:12,095 --> 00:08:13,245
Okay. All right.
You got me.

199
00:08:13,296 --> 00:08:15,597
Look, I'm not--
I'm not a lawyer.

200
00:08:15,682 --> 00:08:17,933
In fact, between you and me,
I'm a complete fraud.

201
00:08:18,018 --> 00:08:21,020
But what I am
is Colonel Mariga's cousin.

202
00:08:23,756 --> 00:08:25,691
On his mother's side.

203
00:08:25,758 --> 00:08:26,775
- All right.
- Okay, all right!

204
00:08:26,860 --> 00:08:27,977
All right,
you don't believe me?

205
00:08:28,061 --> 00:08:30,729
That's fine.
Just do me a favor, okay?

206
00:08:30,780 --> 00:08:33,032
Give him this photo
of him and my Uncle Stephen.

207
00:08:35,285 --> 00:08:38,454
Then let him decide
if he wants to talk to me.

208
00:08:39,739 --> 00:08:40,990
Louis, how did you
get in here?

209
00:08:41,074 --> 00:08:42,291
I told them
I was your uncle.

210
00:08:42,375 --> 00:08:43,659
Though how they could believe
that we share

211
00:08:43,743 --> 00:08:44,827
the same DNA is beyond me.

212
00:08:44,911 --> 00:08:47,162
This is about your trial,
isn't it?

213
00:08:47,247 --> 00:08:48,287
You're goddamn right
it is!

214
00:08:48,298 --> 00:08:49,381
Why the hell
would you do that to me?

215
00:08:49,449 --> 00:08:51,133
I had no choice.
I was subpoenaed.

216
00:08:51,217 --> 00:08:54,286
It was a mock trial.
You could have refused.

217
00:08:54,337 --> 00:08:55,587
What do you want
from me, Louis?

218
00:08:55,638 --> 00:08:56,955
I want to yell at you!

219
00:08:57,007 --> 00:08:58,524
Well, you can't do that
anymore--you fired me.

220
00:08:58,591 --> 00:09:00,059
Is that what this
whole thing was all about?

221
00:09:00,126 --> 00:09:02,261
You're damn right it was.
And you want to know the truth?

222
00:09:02,312 --> 00:09:03,979
When I found out
about your stupid trial,

223
00:09:04,064 --> 00:09:05,464
I called Nigel
and volunteered.

224
00:09:05,515 --> 00:09:07,299
How dare you?

225
00:09:07,350 --> 00:09:09,401
Me firing you was business.

226
00:09:09,469 --> 00:09:11,320
You bringing up the death
of my cat--

227
00:09:11,404 --> 00:09:12,821
that was personal.

228
00:09:12,906 --> 00:09:14,823
You made me take care
of that stupid cat.

229
00:09:14,908 --> 00:09:16,825
I'm allergic.
It could have killed me.

230
00:09:16,910 --> 00:09:18,327
And when that cat did die,

231
00:09:18,411 --> 00:09:20,829
not only did you never tell me
that it wasn't my fault,

232
00:09:20,914 --> 00:09:23,648
you then fired me
in front of my very best friend.

233
00:09:23,700 --> 00:09:26,585
If that's not personal,
then I don't know what is.

234
00:09:26,652 --> 00:09:28,921
Now get the hell
out of my office.

235
00:09:28,988 --> 00:09:32,124
I will.

236
00:09:32,175 --> 00:09:34,927
But before I do,

237
00:09:34,994 --> 00:09:37,046
I have some personal news
for you

238
00:09:37,130 --> 00:09:40,382
about how your firing
really went down.

239
00:09:43,269 --> 00:09:46,355
Ah, I love this.
We'd just won the championship.

240
00:09:46,439 --> 00:09:47,689
Might I get a copy?

241
00:09:47,774 --> 00:09:49,691
Yeah, I'll get one
framed for you.

242
00:09:49,776 --> 00:09:51,360
You can look at it
in the ten minutes

243
00:09:51,444 --> 00:09:52,861
before they
put you to death.

244
00:09:52,946 --> 00:09:54,679
The photograph
proves nothing.

245
00:09:54,731 --> 00:09:58,200
Trust me, there's a whole
lot more where that came from.

246
00:09:58,284 --> 00:10:01,570
We know all about the ties
between you and Stephen.

247
00:10:01,654 --> 00:10:02,905
Then bring them up.

248
00:10:02,989 --> 00:10:04,957
But I made a deal
to testify against Ava,

249
00:10:05,024 --> 00:10:06,458
and that is what
I'm going to do.

250
00:10:06,526 --> 00:10:07,960
No, you made a deal
to put away

251
00:10:08,027 --> 00:10:10,045
the person responsible
for ordering these killings,

252
00:10:10,130 --> 00:10:12,247
and I suggest you do that
while you still can.

253
00:10:12,332 --> 00:10:13,549
Young man...

254
00:10:13,633 --> 00:10:16,051
If your intention is to shake
my testimony,

255
00:10:16,136 --> 00:10:17,369
that is not
going to happen.

256
00:10:17,420 --> 00:10:18,887
It doesn't need
to happen,

257
00:10:18,972 --> 00:10:21,757
'cause once we prove
that you're lying about Ava,

258
00:10:21,841 --> 00:10:23,425
Cameron Dennis is going
to cancel your deal,

259
00:10:23,510 --> 00:10:25,811
and you're gonna come to me
begging for help.

260
00:10:28,815 --> 00:10:30,766
Do you think
you're the scariest man

261
00:10:30,850 --> 00:10:32,101
I've ever sat across from?

262
00:10:32,185 --> 00:10:34,736
I know
you're not scared of me.

263
00:10:34,821 --> 00:10:37,573
But you are scared
of your own people,

264
00:10:37,657 --> 00:10:39,324
and you should be,

265
00:10:39,392 --> 00:10:40,576
because you and I
both know

266
00:10:40,660 --> 00:10:43,395
they're gonna kill you
the minute you get back.

267
00:10:43,446 --> 00:10:46,064
That I know Stephen doesn't
mean I'm lying about Ava.

268
00:10:46,116 --> 00:10:47,199
But you are.

269
00:10:47,250 --> 00:10:49,334
Ah, and you can see
into my soul.

270
00:10:49,402 --> 00:10:51,336
It doesn't take a fortune
teller to know you're lying.

271
00:10:51,404 --> 00:10:53,905
And it doesn't take one
to know that if you had proof,

272
00:10:53,957 --> 00:10:55,841
you wouldn't be here
talking to me.

273
00:10:58,344 --> 00:11:00,579
So you're not protecting
Stephen out of principle.

274
00:11:00,630 --> 00:11:02,598
I'm not a man
of principle.

275
00:11:02,682 --> 00:11:05,350
I'm a man of expediency.
I get it.

276
00:11:05,418 --> 00:11:07,886
If you change your tune now,
you'll lose the deal you have.

277
00:11:07,937 --> 00:11:12,107
Therefore, I prefer to--
how do you say it--

278
00:11:12,192 --> 00:11:15,110
dance with the one
who brought me.

279
00:11:20,099 --> 00:11:21,617
Harvey, what are you
doing here?

280
00:11:21,701 --> 00:11:23,318
Game time's tomorrow.
We got nothing to say.

281
00:11:23,403 --> 00:11:24,769
I'm here to help you.

282
00:11:24,821 --> 00:11:26,455
I don't need your help.

283
00:11:26,539 --> 00:11:28,440
And you wouldn't be here
unless you need mine.

284
00:11:28,491 --> 00:11:29,908
You're wrong.

285
00:11:29,959 --> 00:11:32,044
I can help you do what you
always said you're all about--

286
00:11:32,111 --> 00:11:33,545
putting bad guys away.

287
00:11:33,613 --> 00:11:35,414
You got a confession for me?

288
00:11:35,465 --> 00:11:37,332
You're going
after the wrong person.

289
00:11:37,417 --> 00:11:39,301
You're her lawyer.
That's what you would say.

290
00:11:39,385 --> 00:11:41,336
I'm not here as her lawyer.

291
00:11:41,421 --> 00:11:42,804
This isn't a speech
for a jury.

292
00:11:42,889 --> 00:11:45,057
I'm here man-to-man to talk
to the guy I used to know.

293
00:11:45,124 --> 00:11:47,176
All right.

294
00:11:47,260 --> 00:11:48,727
Talk.

295
00:11:48,794 --> 00:11:51,847
- I know who really did this.
- Then tell me who it is.

296
00:11:51,931 --> 00:11:53,398
I need a guarantee
you won't use

297
00:11:53,466 --> 00:11:54,799
what I tell you
against David.

298
00:11:54,851 --> 00:11:56,568
If you think
I'm gonna guarantee you

299
00:11:56,636 --> 00:11:58,520
anything but a war tomorrow,

300
00:11:58,605 --> 00:12:00,138
you are sadly mistaken.

301
00:12:00,190 --> 00:12:02,191
I can't tell you who did it,
but somebody else can.

302
00:12:02,275 --> 00:12:03,475
Who?

303
00:12:03,526 --> 00:12:05,977
Colonel Mariga.

304
00:12:06,029 --> 00:12:07,996
Are you kidding me?

305
00:12:08,081 --> 00:12:09,648
I've got the murder weapon.

306
00:12:09,699 --> 00:12:12,150
He says Ava Hessington
pulled his trigger,

307
00:12:12,202 --> 00:12:13,985
and you want me to have him
change his story?

308
00:12:14,037 --> 00:12:15,153
He's only pointing at Ava

309
00:12:15,205 --> 00:12:16,488
because that's what
you want to hear.

310
00:12:16,539 --> 00:12:18,323
Change his deal,
he'll tell you the truth.

311
00:12:18,374 --> 00:12:20,759
He changes his story now,

312
00:12:20,826 --> 00:12:22,961
anything he says
about anybody means shit.

313
00:12:23,012 --> 00:12:24,546
It means shit in court,
but if you are

314
00:12:24,631 --> 00:12:27,883
who you say you are,
it should mean something to you.

315
00:12:27,967 --> 00:12:29,384
You know what, Harvey?

316
00:12:29,469 --> 00:12:32,104
I believe that you believe
she's innocent,

317
00:12:32,171 --> 00:12:33,532
and if you can convince me
of that,

318
00:12:33,606 --> 00:12:35,557
I won't go after her,
but I'm not gonna guarantee

319
00:12:35,642 --> 00:12:37,693
I won't use what you say
before I hear it.

320
00:12:37,777 --> 00:12:40,512
- You want me to just trust you?
- That's what you're asking me.

321
00:12:40,563 --> 00:12:43,398
But if you think that I'm gonna
kneecap my star witness

322
00:12:43,483 --> 00:12:46,652
the day before the trial,
you are out of your mind.

323
00:12:50,659 --> 00:12:51,779
Harold.

324
00:12:51,780 --> 00:12:53,063
What's up, man?
it's good to see you.

325
00:12:53,148 --> 00:12:54,548
I thought
you were my friend.

326
00:12:54,616 --> 00:12:56,116
I am.
What the hell?

327
00:12:56,184 --> 00:12:58,018
Friends don't say they tried
to save your job

328
00:12:58,069 --> 00:13:00,520
when, really,
they hung you out to dry.

329
00:13:00,572 --> 00:13:01,855
So it's true.

330
00:13:01,907 --> 00:13:03,374
Look, Harold,
I didn't mean to--

331
00:13:03,458 --> 00:13:05,209
You know what? Save whatever
bullshit explanation you have,

332
00:13:05,293 --> 00:13:06,544
because I don't want
to hear it.

333
00:13:06,628 --> 00:13:08,462
I'm not trying to give you
a bullshit explanation.

334
00:13:08,529 --> 00:13:09,630
Because there is none.

335
00:13:09,697 --> 00:13:11,215
You got to choose
between you and me,

336
00:13:11,299 --> 00:13:12,532
and you chose yourself.

337
00:13:13,032 --> 00:13:14,482
And then you lied to me
about it.

338
00:13:14,533 --> 00:13:15,533
Yes, Harold, I did.

339
00:13:15,618 --> 00:13:16,778
And then after I lied to you,

340
00:13:16,786 --> 00:13:19,671
I got you a job
at a huge, powerful firm.

341
00:13:19,755 --> 00:13:21,256
Yeah, you got me that job
so I'd owe you one

342
00:13:21,323 --> 00:13:22,257
when the time came.

343
00:13:22,324 --> 00:13:23,491
I got you that job

344
00:13:23,542 --> 00:13:25,159
because I thought you deserved
a second chance.

345
00:13:25,211 --> 00:13:27,679
And then you came calling
when you needed a lawsuit filed

346
00:13:27,763 --> 00:13:29,664
to get rid of your witnesses
in your murder trial.

347
00:13:29,715 --> 00:13:31,132
I trusted you
with that lawsuit

348
00:13:31,183 --> 00:13:32,550
because I thought
you were a competent attorney.

349
00:13:32,635 --> 00:13:34,886
And you were more than happy
to take it.

350
00:13:34,970 --> 00:13:37,555
And that murder trial you just
mentioned is about to start.

351
00:13:37,640 --> 00:13:39,891
So you can choose to be
pissed off with me or move on.

352
00:13:39,975 --> 00:13:42,610
But right now
I have a job to do.

353
00:13:48,451 --> 00:13:50,201
- Rachel.
- Louis, what did you do?

354
00:13:50,286 --> 00:13:51,703
What do you mean?
What is this?

355
00:13:51,787 --> 00:13:53,905
Fairfield Computers
is being sued.

356
00:13:53,989 --> 00:13:55,790
- How's that my fault?
- Because they're your client,

357
00:13:55,858 --> 00:13:57,459
and the attorney of record
is Harold Gunderson.

358
00:13:57,526 --> 00:14:00,128
He also sent
a settlement offer.

359
00:14:00,195 --> 00:14:02,881
He wants to pick
a fight with me.

360
00:14:02,965 --> 00:14:04,365
He's gonna regret
the day he was born.

361
00:14:04,417 --> 00:14:05,917
Aren't you the one
who picked a fight with him?

362
00:14:06,001 --> 00:14:07,886
Rachel, whose side
are you on?

363
00:14:07,970 --> 00:14:09,220
Don't answer that question.

364
00:14:12,758 --> 00:14:14,392
You shouldn't be here.

365
00:14:14,477 --> 00:14:17,896
Stephen said that we're
no different than he is.

366
00:14:17,980 --> 00:14:19,931
I need to see you show him
that he's wrong.

367
00:14:20,015 --> 00:14:22,150
This isn't his trial.
It's Ava's.

368
00:14:22,217 --> 00:14:23,718
You're not gonna put him
on the stand?

369
00:14:23,769 --> 00:14:25,570
You said you were gonna
make him pay.

370
00:14:25,654 --> 00:14:28,156
Donna, I will,
but now is not the time.

371
00:14:28,223 --> 00:14:30,391
Then when?
Because he killed people,

372
00:14:30,443 --> 00:14:33,161
and if we let him
get away with it...

373
00:14:33,228 --> 00:14:35,447
Then maybe we are
no different than he is.

374
00:14:37,032 --> 00:14:39,501
Had these insurgents
had their way,

375
00:14:39,568 --> 00:14:41,252
they would have blown up
the pipeline.

376
00:14:41,337 --> 00:14:44,172
Instead, Ms. Hessington
retained a valuable asset,

377
00:14:44,239 --> 00:14:47,258
and I, in turn, was compensated
for a job well done.

378
00:14:47,343 --> 00:14:51,129
And this compensation came
directly from Ava Hessington?

379
00:14:51,213 --> 00:14:52,597
Yes.

380
00:14:52,681 --> 00:14:54,883
She specifically directed you
to kill people?

381
00:14:56,102 --> 00:14:57,302
Yes.

382
00:14:57,386 --> 00:14:59,253
One more thing,
Colonel Mariga--

383
00:14:59,305 --> 00:15:01,439
do you and I have a deal
for you to testify

384
00:15:01,524 --> 00:15:04,109
in exchange
for a more lenient sentence?

385
00:15:04,193 --> 00:15:06,093
Yes.

386
00:15:06,145 --> 00:15:07,428
And why should
the jury believe

387
00:15:07,480 --> 00:15:09,764
that you aren't making this up
to save yourself?

388
00:15:09,815 --> 00:15:12,200
Because if what I say to you
proves to be a lie,

389
00:15:12,267 --> 00:15:14,435
you'll send me back home,

390
00:15:14,487 --> 00:15:17,122
where I will be dead
within minutes.

391
00:15:17,206 --> 00:15:18,456
No further questions.

392
00:15:22,828 --> 00:15:24,245
Ten minutes recess.

393
00:15:24,296 --> 00:15:26,297
Why didn't you just
jump right in there?

394
00:15:26,382 --> 00:15:28,299
I get it--
you read a book that says

395
00:15:28,384 --> 00:15:29,617
you don't let the jury
sit with things.

396
00:15:29,668 --> 00:15:30,718
The only problem is...

397
00:15:30,786 --> 00:15:31,886
We're not inside
of a book.

398
00:15:31,954 --> 00:15:33,421
And I don't want
to seem defensive.

399
00:15:33,472 --> 00:15:35,512
Harvey, we still have
a ton of shit to hit him with.

400
00:15:35,558 --> 00:15:37,792
Were you in there?
They're buying what he's saying.

401
00:15:37,843 --> 00:15:39,283
Then we make them
buy something else.

402
00:15:39,311 --> 00:15:40,895
We got a pair of aces.

403
00:15:40,963 --> 00:15:42,347
If the jury believes that
Cameron's got three of a kind,

404
00:15:42,431 --> 00:15:44,632
we're not gonna win.
We can't go after Stephen.

405
00:15:44,683 --> 00:15:46,017
Cameron
won't go after Ava

406
00:15:46,101 --> 00:15:47,652
if I can convince him
it was Stephen.

407
00:15:47,736 --> 00:15:49,070
- You went to Cameron?
- Yes.

408
00:15:49,137 --> 00:15:50,638
And you're going
to trust him?

409
00:15:50,689 --> 00:15:53,140
I'm not sure
we have another choice.

410
00:15:55,945 --> 00:15:57,529
If you're thinking
what I think you're thinking,

411
00:15:57,613 --> 00:15:59,113
don't.

412
00:15:59,165 --> 00:16:01,032
I'm thinking I'd like
to rip your face off.

413
00:16:01,116 --> 00:16:02,717
You get Mariga
to point the finger at me,

414
00:16:02,785 --> 00:16:04,819
I will point it
straight at Ava.

415
00:16:04,870 --> 00:16:07,589
Stephen, Jessica
doesn't respond well to threats.

416
00:16:07,656 --> 00:16:09,090
Well, I don't make threats.

417
00:16:09,157 --> 00:16:11,209
I give warnings.

418
00:16:11,293 --> 00:16:13,294
You've been warned.

419
00:16:19,218 --> 00:16:21,553
Mr. Specter...

420
00:16:21,637 --> 00:16:24,272
I have no questions
for Colonel Mariga, Your Honor,

421
00:16:24,339 --> 00:16:26,340
but I'd like to call
a rebuttal witness.

422
00:16:26,392 --> 00:16:28,193
Harvey, come on,
you know what he's gonna say.

423
00:16:28,194 --> 00:16:29,894
I don't care
what he's gonna say.

424
00:16:29,979 --> 00:16:31,896
He's talking to the jury.
I'm talking to Cameron Dennis.

425
00:16:31,981 --> 00:16:36,067
The defense calls
Stephen Huntley to the stand.

426
00:16:36,151 --> 00:16:38,887
What has Stephen Huntley
got to do with this?

427
00:16:38,954 --> 00:16:40,538
Harvey knows
what he's doing.

428
00:16:40,623 --> 00:16:41,906
This is what
you wanted to sell me--

429
00:16:41,991 --> 00:16:43,208
a lawyer from your own
goddamn firm?

430
00:16:43,292 --> 00:16:44,572
You want to put away
the bad guy?

431
00:16:44,627 --> 00:16:47,045
I'm about to hand him to you
on a silver platter.

432
00:16:47,129 --> 00:16:50,381
Mr. Huntley,
did you work at the law firm

433
00:16:50,466 --> 00:16:52,634
headed by Edward Darby
last year?

434
00:16:52,701 --> 00:16:54,302
Yes.

435
00:16:54,369 --> 00:16:56,971
Did Mr. Darby ask you
to solve any problems

436
00:16:57,039 --> 00:16:58,473
for Hessington Oil

437
00:16:58,540 --> 00:17:00,675
regarding their pipeline
in the E.I.R.?

438
00:17:00,726 --> 00:17:02,810
I decline to answer under
my fifth amendment rights.

439
00:17:02,878 --> 00:17:05,063
The right
against self-incrimination.

440
00:17:05,147 --> 00:17:06,514
How long have you known
Colonel Mariga?

441
00:17:06,565 --> 00:17:07,732
I decline to answer.

442
00:17:07,816 --> 00:17:09,601
Is it true that you
went to school with him

443
00:17:09,685 --> 00:17:10,935
at the University
of Cape Town?

444
00:17:11,020 --> 00:17:12,053
I decline to answer.

445
00:17:12,104 --> 00:17:13,521
Well, let me refresh
your memory.

446
00:17:13,572 --> 00:17:15,490
You were teammates
on a championship rugby team.

447
00:17:15,557 --> 00:17:17,575
Objection.
Counsel is testifying.

448
00:17:17,660 --> 00:17:19,110
The witness is hostile,
Your Honor.

449
00:17:19,194 --> 00:17:21,029
Hostile? They work
at the same law firm.

450
00:17:21,080 --> 00:17:22,530
He was fired yesterday.

451
00:17:22,581 --> 00:17:24,198
Gentlemen, approach.

452
00:17:27,202 --> 00:17:29,420
He's making things up
to create reasonable doubt.

453
00:17:29,505 --> 00:17:31,923
I'm bringing things up,
so you'll see the truth.

454
00:17:32,007 --> 00:17:34,676
The only thing tying Ava to this
is Mariga's testimony.

455
00:17:34,743 --> 00:17:37,595
You only have Mariga because
you tapped Stephen's phone.

456
00:17:37,680 --> 00:17:38,913
That's a ridiculous
accusation.

457
00:17:38,964 --> 00:17:40,098
Cameron, please.

458
00:17:40,182 --> 00:17:42,934
Why did he call him?
How did he call him?

459
00:17:43,018 --> 00:17:44,435
Enough.

460
00:17:44,520 --> 00:17:46,554
You're on a short leash,
Mr. Specter.

461
00:17:46,605 --> 00:17:49,090
The gentleman
invoked his rights.

462
00:17:53,428 --> 00:17:55,947
Mr. Huntley, did you meet
with your old friend

463
00:17:56,031 --> 00:17:58,599
Emmanuel Mariga
and direct him

464
00:17:58,651 --> 00:18:01,703
to kill the opponent
of Hessington Oil's pipeline

465
00:18:01,770 --> 00:18:04,238
without Ava Hessington's
knowledge?

466
00:18:04,290 --> 00:18:07,208
I decline to answer.

467
00:18:07,275 --> 00:18:08,876
I have
no further questions.

468
00:18:08,944 --> 00:18:11,629
Mr. Dennis,
do you have any questions?

469
00:18:13,248 --> 00:18:15,950
Mr. Dennis.

470
00:18:21,090 --> 00:18:23,391
Mr. Huntley,
until you were let go,

471
00:18:23,458 --> 00:18:26,627
you worked at the same firm
as Mr. Specter, correct?

472
00:18:26,679 --> 00:18:28,295
Yes.

473
00:18:28,347 --> 00:18:31,149
And his job today
is to give this jury

474
00:18:31,233 --> 00:18:35,186
cause to doubt that
his client is the murderer?

475
00:18:35,270 --> 00:18:37,138
- Yes.
- In your experience...

476
00:18:37,189 --> 00:18:39,691
Is pointing the finger
at someone else

477
00:18:39,775 --> 00:18:41,308
a good strategy?

478
00:18:41,360 --> 00:18:43,578
It can be
an excellent strategy.

479
00:18:43,645 --> 00:18:46,080
And why do you think
that Mr. Specter

480
00:18:46,148 --> 00:18:47,865
is pointing the finger
at you?

481
00:18:47,950 --> 00:18:49,834
Well, maybe it has something
to do with the fact

482
00:18:49,918 --> 00:18:52,987
that a few weeks ago
Ms. Hessington approached me

483
00:18:53,038 --> 00:18:54,372
and asked me
to bribe witnesses

484
00:18:54,456 --> 00:18:56,124
who were about
to testify against her,

485
00:18:56,175 --> 00:18:57,542
and I refused.

486
00:18:57,626 --> 00:18:59,210
And if you think
I'm lying under oath,

487
00:18:59,294 --> 00:19:02,213
then, please,
ask Mr. Specter.

488
00:19:02,297 --> 00:19:03,598
He knows that's the truth.

489
00:19:03,665 --> 00:19:06,551
And a woman who bribes
witnesses against her

490
00:19:06,635 --> 00:19:07,769
is not innocent.

491
00:19:07,836 --> 00:19:08,886
Objection.

492
00:19:08,971 --> 00:19:10,838
Withdrawn.
One last thing.

493
00:19:10,889 --> 00:19:13,941
Did the defendant
ask you to arrange a meeting

494
00:19:14,009 --> 00:19:16,310
with Colonel Mariga
where she she would pay him

495
00:19:16,362 --> 00:19:19,731
millions of dollars
in exchange for...

496
00:19:19,815 --> 00:19:21,733
Killing opponents
of her pipeline?

497
00:19:21,817 --> 00:19:24,035
I decline to answer.

498
00:19:24,119 --> 00:19:27,038
Can't blame a guy
for trying.

499
00:19:27,122 --> 00:19:28,740
No further questions.

