00:30:11,024 --> 00:30:12,591
It's from <i>The Breakfast Club,</i>
asshole.

755
00:30:12,642 --> 00:30:14,443
Not all of us only watch
<i>The Sound Of Music.</i>

756
00:30:14,527 --> 00:30:16,979
You little bastard.
You just crossed a line.

757
00:30:17,063 --> 00:30:19,264
Julie Andrews
is a national treasure.

758
00:30:19,315 --> 00:30:21,650
Maybe your client
would be better off with her.

759
00:30:21,735 --> 00:30:22,735
Maybe they would be.

760
00:30:22,786 --> 00:30:24,936
But she isn't here.
And I am.

761
00:30:24,988 --> 00:30:27,105
And here are a few
of my favorite things--

762
00:30:27,157 --> 00:30:28,991
countersuit for slander,

763
00:30:29,075 --> 00:30:30,993
motion to decertify class,

764
00:30:31,077 --> 00:30:32,795
motion for summary judgment,

765
00:30:32,879 --> 00:30:35,080
change of venue, sanctions,

766
00:30:35,131 --> 00:30:38,300
depositions, discovery!

767
00:30:38,385 --> 00:30:40,719
Great use
of folders there, Louis.

768
00:30:40,787 --> 00:30:42,504
Too bad none of them
are gonna work.

769
00:30:42,589 --> 00:30:44,122
Well, they may not work
on the case,

770
00:30:44,174 --> 00:30:46,308
but they're definitely
gonna work on you.

771
00:30:46,393 --> 00:30:47,893
What are you talking about?

772
00:30:47,960 --> 00:30:49,961
Oh, I'm talking
about you may win in the end,

773
00:30:50,013 --> 00:30:52,848
but it won't justify you
spending every waking minute

774
00:30:52,932 --> 00:30:54,349
of your life
on this bullshit,

775
00:30:54,434 --> 00:30:57,352
instead of doing everything else
you've been assigned to do.

776
00:30:57,437 --> 00:30:59,738
- You'd do that to me?
- I won't be doing it to you.

777
00:30:59,806 --> 00:31:01,740
I'll be doing it
for Bratton Gould.

778
00:31:01,808 --> 00:31:03,242
And you'll be laughed
out of there

779
00:31:03,309 --> 00:31:04,949
the same way you were laughed
out of here.

780
00:31:04,977 --> 00:31:06,578
- Louis--
- We got nothing left to say!

781
00:31:06,646 --> 00:31:08,330
Drop the suit
by the end of the week,

782
00:31:08,415 --> 00:31:10,699
or one of my associates
will see you in court.

783
00:31:10,784 --> 00:31:11,834
Get out!

784
00:31:25,215 --> 00:31:27,349
I don't want him here.

785
00:31:27,434 --> 00:31:30,686
Ava, whatever he did,
he's here to help,

786
00:31:30,770 --> 00:31:32,871
and he's an asset.

787
00:31:32,939 --> 00:31:36,007
Then what does the mighty
Edward Darby have to say?

788
00:31:36,059 --> 00:31:38,060
You're innocent
until proven guilty

789
00:31:38,144 --> 00:31:39,645
beyond a reasonable doubt.

790
00:31:39,696 --> 00:31:40,863
Take the stand.

791
00:31:40,947 --> 00:31:43,315
Any juror that hears you
will have that doubt.

792
00:31:43,366 --> 00:31:44,900
She opens that door,
the first question

793
00:31:44,984 --> 00:31:47,986
Cameron asks is, did she try
and bribe those witnesses?

794
00:31:48,037 --> 00:31:52,908
The answer is yes.
There goes reasonable doubt.

795
00:31:52,992 --> 00:31:54,293
How much did you pay him?

796
00:31:54,360 --> 00:31:56,044
- Cameron.
- Pay who?

797
00:31:56,129 --> 00:31:58,714
Don't play dumb.
Clifford Danner.

798
00:31:58,798 --> 00:32:00,582
Who the hell
is Clifford Danner?

799
00:32:00,667 --> 00:32:03,051
He was an innocent person
that Cameron put behind bars.

800
00:32:03,136 --> 00:32:04,816
And I thought
he would make you see reason.

801
00:32:04,871 --> 00:32:06,054
That has nothing
to do with this.

802
00:32:06,139 --> 00:32:07,706
And I didn't put him
behind bars--you did.

803
00:32:07,757 --> 00:32:09,141
Then I got him out.

804
00:32:09,208 --> 00:32:11,059
Well, you're not getting
her out, because she did it,

805
00:32:11,144 --> 00:32:13,812
and yesterday your own colleague
said that she did it.

806
00:32:13,880 --> 00:32:16,265
He did not say that,
and you know it.

807
00:32:16,349 --> 00:32:18,350
- You willing to take that risk?
- What are you suggesting?

808
00:32:18,401 --> 00:32:19,852
I've worked with him
long enough

809
00:32:19,903 --> 00:32:21,236
to know what he's suggesting.

810
00:32:21,321 --> 00:32:23,155
Cameron Dennis
doesn't go to verdict.

811
00:32:23,222 --> 00:32:24,857
He cuts deals.
Then let me tell you...

812
00:32:24,908 --> 00:32:27,409
About what's
behind door number one--

813
00:32:27,494 --> 00:32:29,060
Eight years.

814
00:32:30,446 --> 00:32:33,499
Eight years instead of forever.
Leave us alone.

815
00:32:33,566 --> 00:32:36,168
Court's in ten minutes.
You have until then.

816
00:32:36,235 --> 00:32:37,569
[Door opens]

817
00:32:37,620 --> 00:32:39,171
Harvey...

818
00:32:39,238 --> 00:32:40,956
He's got us,
and you know it.

819
00:32:41,040 --> 00:32:42,207
No, he doesn't.

820
00:32:42,258 --> 00:32:44,126
She's not going to prison
for one day.

821
00:32:44,210 --> 00:32:46,011
She's going
for the rest of her life

822
00:32:46,078 --> 00:32:47,746
if we don't take this deal.

823
00:32:47,797 --> 00:32:49,431
I am not losing to him.

824
00:32:49,516 --> 00:32:52,250
You-your blood feud

825
00:32:52,302 --> 00:32:54,303
or whatever it is
you have with that man

826
00:32:54,387 --> 00:32:57,306
is what put the target
on my back in the first place.

827
00:32:57,390 --> 00:32:59,942
Ava, we need
to face reality.

828
00:33:00,026 --> 00:33:02,361
She is not taking that deal.

829
00:33:02,428 --> 00:33:05,447
She better, because
she can't buy her way out of it.

830
00:33:05,532 --> 00:33:07,933
And you can't cover up
your way out of it.

831
00:33:07,984 --> 00:33:09,434
- I don't care.
- Well, what's your idea?

832
00:33:09,485 --> 00:33:10,869
Because unless
you're gonna testify

833
00:33:10,937 --> 00:33:13,038
that Stephen did this
without Ava's knowledge,

834
00:33:13,105 --> 00:33:14,239
you can't help.

835
00:33:14,290 --> 00:33:15,991
And as you said,
you have no proof.

836
00:33:16,075 --> 00:33:19,578
So why don't you get out of the
room and let the grown-ups talk?

837
00:33:19,629 --> 00:33:22,497
What if I was
to testify to that?

838
00:33:24,417 --> 00:33:26,001
What are you talking about?

839
00:33:26,085 --> 00:33:28,670
I'm talking about putting
words to a conversation

840
00:33:28,755 --> 00:33:30,973
that should have happened
but didn't.

841
00:33:31,057 --> 00:33:34,476
You'd say that you confronted
Stephen, and he admitted it?

842
00:33:34,561 --> 00:33:37,462
I made this mess.
It's up to me to clear it up.

843
00:33:37,513 --> 00:33:38,964
This isn't gonna help.

844
00:33:39,015 --> 00:33:41,633
You're her old friend coming
to her aid at the last second.

845
00:33:41,684 --> 00:33:42,768
It's a lie.

846
00:33:42,819 --> 00:33:44,186
The jury will see
right through it.

847
00:33:44,270 --> 00:33:45,854
Then we need to make Cameron
believe it.

848
00:33:45,939 --> 00:33:47,856
Harvey, Cameron wants a win.

849
00:33:47,941 --> 00:33:49,858
You need to convince him
this is a win.

850
00:33:49,943 --> 00:33:52,578
Can you do that?

851
00:33:52,645 --> 00:33:55,998
I guess it's the best shot
we have.

852
00:34:06,192 --> 00:34:09,008
I knew you would cave.
With five minutes to spare.

853
00:34:09,716 --> 00:34:11,549
We're not here
to take your offer, Cameron.

854
00:34:11,550 --> 00:34:12,851
We want you to take ours.

855
00:34:12,935 --> 00:34:15,169
Nah, I'm not negotiating.
Eight years is final.

856
00:34:15,221 --> 00:34:16,838
This isn't about making
a deal for Ava.

857
00:34:16,889 --> 00:34:18,273
It's about making
a deal for me.

858
00:34:18,340 --> 00:34:21,175
If he's got something
to say about this,

859
00:34:21,227 --> 00:34:23,278
you should put him
on the stand.

860
00:34:23,345 --> 00:34:27,065
I already trusted you once.
I need your word.

861
00:34:27,149 --> 00:34:29,017
Go ahead.
Off the record.

862
00:34:29,068 --> 00:34:32,487
I instructed Stephen Huntley
to do whatever it took

863
00:34:32,538 --> 00:34:33,905
to get Ava her pipeline,

864
00:34:33,990 --> 00:34:36,741
and I told him
to do it behind her back.

865
00:34:36,826 --> 00:34:38,693
So you authorized
these murders.

866
00:34:38,744 --> 00:34:39,861
Absolutely not.

867
00:34:39,912 --> 00:34:41,529
When I heard people
had been killed,

868
00:34:41,580 --> 00:34:42,747
I confronted him immediately.

869
00:34:42,832 --> 00:34:44,382
And what did he say?

870
00:34:44,467 --> 00:34:46,384
He didn't care
that he'd resorted to murder.

871
00:34:46,469 --> 00:34:48,202
His job
was to get things done.

872
00:34:48,254 --> 00:34:52,257
You just admitted to being
an accessory after the fact.

873
00:34:52,341 --> 00:34:53,925
No, he didn't.

874
00:34:54,010 --> 00:34:58,013
I get it.
Off the record.

875
00:34:58,064 --> 00:34:59,213
What do you want?

876
00:34:59,265 --> 00:35:01,599
Edward pleads
to obstruction of justice--

877
00:35:01,684 --> 00:35:02,984
five years probation.

878
00:35:03,052 --> 00:35:05,103
You drop the charges
against Ava.

879
00:35:05,187 --> 00:35:06,237
And he testifies

880
00:35:06,322 --> 00:35:08,990
at Stephen Huntley's
murder trial.

881
00:35:11,226 --> 00:35:14,228
And why would I swap out Ava
for her minion?

882
00:35:14,280 --> 00:35:18,083
Cameron, you gave us
that offer for a reason.

883
00:35:18,167 --> 00:35:20,568
You're at the finish line--
you can taste the win,

884
00:35:20,619 --> 00:35:23,338
but it's not 100%,
and you know it,

885
00:35:23,405 --> 00:35:25,445
because you're still banking
on an admitted murderer

886
00:35:25,458 --> 00:35:26,958
with an incentive to lie.

887
00:35:27,043 --> 00:35:28,793
I'm giving you
a respected lawyer

888
00:35:28,878 --> 00:35:31,913
with an incentive to keep
his mouth shut.

889
00:35:31,964 --> 00:35:34,415
You know who has
a better chance

890
00:35:34,467 --> 00:35:37,969
at getting you a win.

891
00:35:38,054 --> 00:35:40,772
[Cameron sighs]

892
00:35:42,525 --> 00:35:44,142
Draw up the paperwork.

893
00:36:05,915 --> 00:36:08,466
I thought you never wanted
to see me again.

894
00:36:08,551 --> 00:36:10,284
I thought
about what you said.

895
00:36:10,336 --> 00:36:13,121
What, about the kind
of business your firm does?

896
00:36:13,172 --> 00:36:15,840
Yes.

897
00:36:15,925 --> 00:36:17,892
And I realized that maybe
you're not as bad

898
00:36:17,960 --> 00:36:19,978
as I said you were.

899
00:36:20,062 --> 00:36:22,797
- No?
- No.

900
00:36:24,967 --> 00:36:27,485
You're much worse.

901
00:36:31,574 --> 00:36:34,475
Harvey and Cameron
made a deal to take you down,

902
00:36:34,527 --> 00:36:36,995
and part of that deal
was that I got to be the one

903
00:36:37,079 --> 00:36:39,164
to tell you about it.

904
00:36:43,485 --> 00:36:46,654
I meant it when I said
I never meant to hurt you.

905
00:36:46,705 --> 00:36:49,958
And I meant it when I said
that you make me sick.

906
00:36:56,498 --> 00:36:59,017
[Exhales deeply]

907
00:36:59,101 --> 00:37:00,385
It's all there.

908
00:37:00,469 --> 00:37:03,221
You testify, you get
five years probation.

909
00:37:03,305 --> 00:37:05,690
And he pleads
obstruction of justice.

910
00:37:05,775 --> 00:37:07,525
- What is this?
- What is what?

911
00:37:07,610 --> 00:37:09,527
This says that I forfeit
my license

912
00:37:09,612 --> 00:37:11,529
to practice law
in this country.

913
00:37:11,614 --> 00:37:13,681
Oh, that--that's just
something I added in.

914
00:37:13,732 --> 00:37:15,817
- This is unacceptable.
- Wait a minute.

915
00:37:15,868 --> 00:37:18,019
How could you add that in
if we did the paperwork?

916
00:37:18,070 --> 00:37:20,205
And if he can't practice law
in the country,

917
00:37:20,289 --> 00:37:21,569
he can't be a member
of our firm.

918
00:37:21,574 --> 00:37:25,076
We must have agreed to it
in advance.

919
00:37:25,161 --> 00:37:27,579
You set
this whole thing up.

920
00:37:27,663 --> 00:37:29,547
Jessica set
this whole thing up.

921
00:37:29,632 --> 00:37:31,216
But what's it matter?

922
00:37:31,300 --> 00:37:32,884
You really gonna put this
on Ava

923
00:37:32,968 --> 00:37:34,636
when you can get off
with a slap on the wrist?

924
00:37:34,703 --> 00:37:36,671
I asked you to put aside
your anger.

925
00:37:36,722 --> 00:37:39,841
I did.
You said Ava was family.

926
00:37:39,892 --> 00:37:42,727
The thing about family
is they make it easy

927
00:37:42,812 --> 00:37:46,014
to put you in the position
where you don't have a choice.

928
00:37:46,065 --> 00:37:48,016
Now, you gonna
sign the deal,

929
00:37:48,067 --> 00:37:51,219
or do I just pick up the trial
right where we left off?

930
00:37:55,858 --> 00:37:57,575
You're doing
the right thing, Edward.

931
00:37:57,660 --> 00:38:00,245
We'll worry about the terms
of our dissolution tomorrow.

932
00:38:02,248 --> 00:38:03,898
And, Edward...

933
00:38:03,949 --> 00:38:05,750
We may be getting a divorce,

934
00:38:05,835 --> 00:38:08,453
but I fully intend on keeping
ownership of the house.

935
00:38:14,844 --> 00:38:16,911
Who'd have thought
we'd end up here?

936
00:38:16,962 --> 00:38:18,246
I did.

937
00:38:18,297 --> 00:38:19,964
No, you didn't.

938
00:38:20,049 --> 00:38:21,799
You took a chance
with Clifford Danner,

939
00:38:21,884 --> 00:38:23,301
and you know it.

940
00:38:23,385 --> 00:38:24,969
It wasn't a chance.

941
00:38:25,054 --> 00:38:26,420
I played the man.

942
00:38:26,472 --> 00:38:29,774
And, Cameron, you're not
only about winning.

943
00:38:29,859 --> 00:38:32,277
You're about putting
guilty people away.

944
00:38:32,361 --> 00:38:35,113
[Briefcase lid thuds]

945
00:38:35,197 --> 00:38:37,148
Nice working with you.

946
00:38:37,233 --> 00:38:40,618
Onetime deal.

947
00:38:40,703 --> 00:38:42,143
I guess this means
you're not looking

948
00:38:42,204 --> 00:38:43,371
for another name partner?

949
00:38:43,438 --> 00:38:45,240
Goodbye, Cameron.

950
00:38:52,548 --> 00:38:54,299
Norma said you
had something for me?

951
00:38:54,383 --> 00:38:56,334
I do.

952
00:38:58,721 --> 00:39:00,638
He dropped it.
I win.

953
00:39:00,723 --> 00:39:03,508
[Giggles]
Do you?

954
00:39:05,627 --> 00:39:07,812
What?
What are you talking about?

955
00:39:07,897 --> 00:39:10,965
Why do you hate Harold
so much?

956
00:39:11,016 --> 00:39:12,800
- I don't hate him.
- Yeah, you do...

957
00:39:12,851 --> 00:39:14,352
Because I've never seen you
be as mean to anyone

958
00:39:14,436 --> 00:39:15,653
as you are to him.
Rachel, I-

959
00:39:15,738 --> 00:39:17,906
- don't "Rachel" me.
He's a human being.

960
00:39:17,973 --> 00:39:19,657
What's the matter with you?

961
00:39:25,948 --> 00:39:28,866
When I was a kid
in gym class...

962
00:39:31,453 --> 00:39:33,204
We had to climb the rope.

963
00:39:34,623 --> 00:39:37,158
Every day I tried
really hard,

964
00:39:37,209 --> 00:39:39,377
and every day...

965
00:39:39,461 --> 00:39:41,763
Everyone would laugh at me.

966
00:39:46,802 --> 00:39:50,004
The one thing in my life
that I've always been great at

967
00:39:50,055 --> 00:39:52,690
is training
the associates...

968
00:39:52,775 --> 00:39:55,643
Except for Harold.

969
00:39:55,694 --> 00:39:57,178
He's my failure.

970
00:39:57,229 --> 00:40:00,565
And every time
I look at him, it...

971
00:40:03,786 --> 00:40:05,820
puts me right back
in gym class.

972
00:40:11,410 --> 00:40:13,628
Louis...

973
00:40:13,695 --> 00:40:15,964
Harold's climbing
that rope.

974
00:40:16,031 --> 00:40:17,698
He's succeeding.

975
00:40:17,750 --> 00:40:19,634
And the way
you got this victory

976
00:40:19,701 --> 00:40:22,086
was by going
after his career.

977
00:40:22,171 --> 00:40:25,757
And you're just yanking him
right back down.

978
00:40:38,187 --> 00:40:40,655
We never got this.

979
00:40:40,722 --> 00:40:43,391
Send back his original offer
marked "accepted."

980
00:40:52,167 --> 00:40:55,236
I never want this
spoken of again.

981
00:40:55,287 --> 00:40:57,405
You never want what
spoken of again?

982
00:41:00,376 --> 00:41:02,877
Harvey,
what did Ava have to say?

983
00:41:02,928 --> 00:41:05,213
She'd already left
for the airport.

984
00:41:05,264 --> 00:41:08,299
Someone saves my life,
I might stop to say thank you.

985
00:41:08,384 --> 00:41:09,717
You really blame her

986
00:41:09,768 --> 00:41:11,302
after what this firm
put her through?

987
00:41:11,387 --> 00:41:12,687
When you put it
that way...

988
00:41:12,754 --> 00:41:14,639
It doesn't matter.
It was a huge win.

989
00:41:14,723 --> 00:41:16,257
Go celebrate.
[Elevator bell dings]

990
00:41:16,308 --> 00:41:17,442
Whoa.
Hey, hey.

991
00:41:17,526 --> 00:41:18,926
Don't you mean
"let's go celebrate"?

992
00:41:18,927 --> 00:41:21,095
Am I really the person
you want to celebrate

993
00:41:21,146 --> 00:41:22,980
this big murder-trial
victory with?

994
00:41:23,065 --> 00:41:24,932
I don't know. It depends.
Do you put out?

995
00:41:24,983 --> 00:41:27,435
- Why don't you ask Rachel?
- That's not funny.

996
00:41:27,486 --> 00:41:30,438
[Ambient music]

997
00:41:30,489 --> 00:41:38,446
♪

998
00:41:42,551 --> 00:41:45,636
Harvey.

999
00:41:45,721 --> 00:41:48,423
Donna.

1000
00:41:48,474 --> 00:41:49,623
How'd it go?

1001
00:41:49,675 --> 00:41:52,176
As well as it could.

1002
00:41:55,848 --> 00:41:57,798
Harvey...

1003
00:42:00,352 --> 00:42:02,136
Thank you.

1004
00:42:02,187 --> 00:42:04,655
Why don't you keep the car?

